# IPBuilding (Cursor)

## Purpose

Replace the proprietary IPBox by reverse-engineering controller UDP/1001 and eventually exposing an IPBox-compatible REST API (port 30200) for Home Assistant.

## Authoritative docs (read before deep work)

- `AGENTS.md` — current priorities and immediate tasks
- `resources_and_docs/IPBUILDING_KNOWLEDGE.md` — hardware, topology, REST API, UDP notes, install specifics

## External reference

HA integration (REST client patterns): https://github.com/markminnoye/HA-IPBuilding — `custom_components/ipbuilding/api.py`

## Defaults (lab / prod as documented)

| Role | IP | Port |
|------|-----|------|
| IPBox REST | 10.10.1.1 | 30200 |
| IP200PoE relays UDP | 10.10.1.30 | 1001 |
| IP0300PoE dimmers UDP | 10.10.0.40 | 1001 |

Treat lab IPs as configurable in code; do not hardcode secrets.

## Working style

- Prefer small, testable steps toward UDP command decode and correlation (timestamps, diffs).
- Binary captures and PDFs live under `resources_and_docs/`; do not load huge binaries into context unless analyzing a specific slice.
- This workspace enables the **wireshark-mcp** MCP (see `.cursor/mcp.json`); use it for structured reads/stats on `.pcapng` instead of pulling full captures into the chat.
